  "body": "### Environment\n\n- **Qiskit version**: 2.3 \n- **Python version**: 3.11\n- **Operating system**: Linux\n\n\n### What is happening?\n\nThis is a followup for the discussion [here](https://github.com/Qiskit/qiskit/pull/14166#discussion_r2702334052). Currently, the `FromPyObject` of `QuantumCircuitData` directly accessed the `_data` field (`let circuit_data = ob.getattr(\"_data\")?;`). For the specific case of `BlueprintCircuit` this fails since the circuit lazily builds the `_data` field only as part of the `data` method call.\n\nIn #14166 this is fixed by explicitly calling the `data` method, but given that  this is a unique problem of `BlueprintCircuit` and we can ensure it won't happen in other classes we should probably aim for a more specific solution.\n\n### How can we reproduce the issue?\n\nRunning `TestLoadFromQPY::test_qaoa` test encounters this if Rust QPY is enabled and the fixing line removed.\n\n### What should happen?\n\nEither the current fix stays in place or we perform a dedicated check to see whether we have a `BlueprintCircuit` and act accordingly.\n\n### Any suggestions?\n\n_No response_",
